    ‚îÇ  SCL  ‚óè‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îº‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îº‚îÄ‚îÄ‚óè Pin 2  (GP1) ‚îÇ
    ‚îÇ                 ‚îÇ   YELLOW       ‚îÇ                 ‚îÇ
    ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îò                ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îò
```

### Wire Specifications

**Recommended Wire Colors:**
| Wire | Color | Purpose |
|------|-------|---------|
| VCC  | üî¥ Red | Positive 3.3V power |
| GND  | ‚ö´ Black | Ground |
| SDA  | üîµ Blue | I2C Data |
| SCL  | üü° Yellow | I2C Clock |

**Wire Gauge:** 24-28 AWG (0.2-0.5mm¬≤)
**Maximum Length:** 1 meter (longer may need pull-up resistors)

### I2C Pull-up Resistors

Most BME280 breakout boards have **built-in pull-up resistors** (typically 4.7kŒ© or 10kŒ©).

**If your board doesn't have pull-ups, add them:**
```
3.3V ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚î¨‚îÄ‚îÄ 4.7kŒ© ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚î¨‚îÄ‚îÄ SDA (GP0)
       ‚îÇ           ‚îÇ
       ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ 4.7kŒ© ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚î¥‚îÄ‚îÄ SCL (GP1)
```

### I2C Address

BME280 can have two addresses:
- **0x76** (Default - SDO pin to GND)
- **0x77** (Alternate - SDO pin to VCC)

**Check your address:**
```python
from machine import I2C, Pin
i2c = I2C(0, sda=Pin(0), scl=Pin(1))
print(hex(i2c.scan()[0]))  # Will show 0x76 or 0x77
```

Update `config.py` if needed:
```python
BME280_I2C_ADDR = 0x76  # or 0x77
```

