### Minimal Setup Features

**What you get:**
- ‚úÖ Temperature, humidity, pressure readings
- ‚úÖ WiFi connectivity and cloud upload
- ‚úÖ All core functionality
- ‚úÖ Easy to build and test

**What you don't get:**
- ‚ùå Battery backup
- ‚ùå Solar charging
- ‚ùå Battery monitoring
- ‚ùå Outdoor deployment (needs power outlet)

**Perfect for:**
- üè† Indoor weather monitoring
- üß™ Prototyping and testing
- üéì Learning and experimentation
- üíª Development

### Bill of Materials (Minimal)

| Item | Cost | Where to Buy |
|------|------|--------------|
| Raspberry Pi Pico W | $6 | Adafruit, Amazon, Pimoroni |
| BME280 Module | $8-15 | Amazon, eBay, AliExpress |
| USB Cable | $3 | Any micro-USB cable |
| Jumper Wires (4) | $2 | Any electronics store |
| **Total** | **~$20** | |

## ‚ö° Section 5: Complete Solar-Powered System

Full outdoor deployment with continuous operation!

