### Solar System Features

**Advantages:**
- ‚úÖ Continuous operation (no recharging)
- ‚úÖ True outdoor deployment
- ‚úÖ Battery backup for night/clouds
- ‚úÖ Battery monitoring and protection
- ‚úÖ Fully autonomous

**Power Budget:**
- ‚òÄÔ∏è Solar input: 6V √ó 1.5A = 9W (peak sun)
- üîã Battery: 3.7V √ó 3000mAh = 11.1Wh
- üíª Pico consumption: 50-100mAh per day
- üìä Result: 30+ days battery backup, infinite with sun

### Bill of Materials (Solar)

| Item | Qty | Cost | Notes |
|------|-----|------|-------|
| Raspberry Pi Pico W | 1 | $6 | WiFi microcontroller |
| BME280 Module | 1 | $8-15 | I2C sensor |
| Solar Panel 6V 10W | 1 | $10-20 | Weatherproof |
| 18650 Battery 3000mAh | 1 | $5-10 | Protected cell |
| TP4056 Charge Controller | 1 | $3-5 | With load sharing |
| 5V Buck-Boost Regulator | 1 | $3-8 | Pololu or similar |
| 10kŒ© Resistors (2) | 2 | $0.20 | 1% tolerance |
| Weatherproof Enclosure | 1 | $10-20 | IP65+ rated |
| Jumper Wires | 10 | $2 | Various lengths |
| USB Cable | 1 | $3 | For programming |
| **Total** | | **~$50-80** | |

